Living with uncertainty is hard! Our brain perceives ambiguity as a threat and tries to protect us by stimulating us to seek information about the future and focus on creating certainty. As a result, most innovations and transformations come to pass only after stepping into the unknown. In fact, uncertainty and possibility are two sides of the same coin, and it is our individual resiliency and positive outlook that help unravel one instead of the other.

 

The Women@Microsoft India ERG is excited to kick off Women's History Month (WHM), 2023 with a panel discussion on“Navigating through Uncertainty” with Aparna Gupta - GM Customer Success, Mayurika Singh – Director Support Eng. Mgmt., Sundeep Kunchala - Partner Group Manager and Vivek Adholia – Services Practice Leader.Come, take a front row seat in a conversation with our esteemed and experienced panel and be inspired from their insights on building resiliency and staying positive. You can get the conversation going by sharing your questions at the link below.
